The paper deals with the asymptotic performance of codes viewed as modules in a ring, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves factorizations of polynomials over finite fields, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and number theory (cs.NT). The use of self-dual codes is a topic in coding theory (cs.DS), and the paper also derives a modified Varshamov-Gilbert bound, which is a topic in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
